# Payments Ledger View Specification

## Purpose
Definir el comportamiento funcional de la vista de ledger de pagos por paciente en `/payments/[id]`, para una primera entrega de solo UI con datos mock y sin acciones transaccionales.

## Requirements

### Requirement: Patient Ledger Route Rendering
The system MUST render a private patient ledger view at route `/payments/[id]` and SHALL resolve the patient identifier from the route segment.

#### Scenario: Open ledger detail page
- GIVEN a user is authenticated in the private area
- WHEN the user navigates to `/payments/123`
- THEN the ledger page is rendered in the private layout context
- AND the page receives `id=123` as the active patient reference

#### Scenario: Route id with no matching mock data
- GIVEN the route id does not exist in the mock dataset
- WHEN the user opens `/payments/[id]`
- THEN the page still renders without runtime errors
- AND ledger sections show empty-state compatible data

### Requirement: Analytics Cards with Coverage Progress
The system MUST show analytical summary cards using existing shadcn card components, and MUST use shadcn/ui `progress` component to represent covered percentage.

#### Scenario: Render analytics summary
- GIVEN mock ledger totals are available
- WHEN the page renders analytics
- THEN summary values are displayed in card-based blocks
- AND covered percentage is visualized with a progress bar

#### Scenario: Zero covered percentage
- GIVEN covered amount is zero
- WHEN analytics are rendered
- THEN the progress value is shown as 0%
- AND the progress indicator remains valid and visible

### Requirement: History Table Columns Contract
The system MUST render the payment history table with ONLY these columns: `método`, `monto`, `fecha`.

#### Scenario: Table headers contract
- GIVEN ledger movements are loaded from mock data
- WHEN the history table is displayed
- THEN only método, monto, fecha headers are present
- AND no extra operational or CTA columns are rendered

#### Scenario: Empty history state
- GIVEN the selected patient has no movements
- WHEN the history table section loads
- THEN the table structure remains valid
- AND an empty result state is shown without adding new columns

### Requirement: Paginated History Navigation
The system MUST paginate the history table and SHALL update the visible slice according to active page state.

#### Scenario: Navigate to next page
- GIVEN movement count exceeds one page size
- WHEN the user selects the next page
- THEN table rows update to the corresponding page slice
- AND pagination state remains consistent with current page index

#### Scenario: Page out of bounds normalization
- GIVEN an invalid page value is requested
- WHEN pagination state is resolved
- THEN the page index is normalized to a valid range
- AND the view remains stable without crashing

### Requirement: UI-Only and No-CTA Scope
The system MUST operate with typed mock data only, MUST NOT require database/API calls, and MUST NOT render CTAs (create/edit/charge/export/row actions).

#### Scenario: Load ledger without backend
- GIVEN no backend connectivity is available
- WHEN the page is opened
- THEN all ledger content is sourced from in-memory mock data
- AND no data-fetch dependency blocks rendering

#### Scenario: CTA prohibition
- GIVEN the ledger view is rendered
- WHEN the user inspects interactive elements
- THEN informational controls for pagination only are available
- AND transactional/action CTAs are absent

### Requirement: Separation of Logic and Presentation
The system MUST separate domain logic into hooks and SHALL keep rendering concerns in presentational components.

#### Scenario: Hook-driven composition
- GIVEN ledger state and derived metrics are needed
- WHEN page composition is implemented
- THEN derivation/pagination/mock orchestration live in hook modules
- AND presentational components consume typed props without owning domain logic
